text: A cute thing about Dr. Ray Peat is in emails sometimes he refers to marijuana as "the weed". "Have you been using too much of the weed?" But he did mention from the cannabis compounds he thought "CBDA" is the more generally protective one and linked a study on COX-2 inhibition...

I think the logic of CBDA being better than CBD is the same as supplementing Pregnenolone instead of some downstream metabolite, the precursor substances generally being more broadly protective, e.g. Cholesterol.
It's still funny that Paul Saladino got one deaged by a single interview with Haidut and immediately 100% fully switched to the Ray Peat paradigm
